r price (price\\_new) information will show down the bottom.\r\n\r\nThe solution is going to involve changing a fair bit of JavaScript (I believe `public/javascripts/app.vehicle_selector.js` is the culprit).\r\n\r\nHopefully that's enough information to get started, let me know when you have any questions.	0	1	2012-10-18 08:49:43.111517	2013-01-25 12:05:52.510218	<p>Nate says:</p>\n\n<p>At the moment Vehicle Selector UI handles used cars only, we&#39;d like to update it to support new cars as well.</p>\n\n<p>For Motor Vehicle Finance app forms, on the Vehicle Details page we have a Vehicle Selector section. In this section a user can select a vehicle using several dropdowns, e.g. Year, Make, Model, etc. The data is populated using the Glass Guide database, which gets updated on a monthly basis. The Glass Guide database we get sent contains information for both new and used vehicles, and we store the new/used information in the same vehicle record.</p>\n\n<p>We store the Glass Guide database across the following tables:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>glass_kilometres </li>\n<li>glass_kilometres_vehicles </li>\n<li>glass_option_values </li>\n<li>glass_options </li>\n<li>glass_option_details </li>\n<li>glass_vehicles</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We store the selected vehicle details in the following tables:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>glasses_selected_vehicles </li>\n<li>glasses_selected_factory_options</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>A vehicle in the glass_vehicles table always contains used vehicle information (i.e. price_p, price_pp and price_ppp). Rows that populate the price_new field are also new vehicle records. In our system at the moment we have approx 31050 used vehicles, approx 2350 of these populate the price_new field (these figures will be doubling soon).</p>\n\n<p>Important database fields:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>price_ppp is the used dealer Retail price </li>\n<li>price_pp is the used dealer Trade price </li>\n<li>price_p is the used dealer Trade low price </li>\n<li>price_new is the new dealer price</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Tasks:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Reverse the order of the Year select options. </li>\n<li>Add &quot;New&quot; option to the top of the Year select. </li>\n<li>When an existing Year (e.g. 2012) is chosen, everything will operate as it currently does. The Retail, Trade and Trade low information will show down the bottom. </li>\n<li>When &quot;New&quot; is chosen, it will only populate the dropdowns with new vehicles (i.e. the 2350 vehicles). Only the new dealer price (price_new) information will show down the bottom.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The solution is going to involve changing a fair bit of JavaScript (I believe <code>public/javascripts/app.vehicle_selector.js</code> is the culprit).</p>\n\n<p>Hopefully that&#39;s enough information to get started, let me know when you have any questions.</p>	\N	\N	\N
